						<span>Introduction of Course</span><br/><br/>
						M.Tech. (Mechanical Engineering) is a full-time degree course, approved by AICTE, New Delhi, and Govt of Punjab and has an affiliation to Punjab Technical University (PTU), Jalandhar.<br/><br/>
						
						<span>Career Prospect of M.Tech (ME) Course</span><br/><br/>
						There is an ample of career opportunities in the field of mechanical engineering. Mechanical professionals basically deal with designing, creation and maintenance of industrial machines used to manufacture goods. Certainly, mechanical experts are required in various public and private sector companies - space research organization, technical wings of armed forces, chemical, steel plants, electronics, automobiles, oil exploration and refining and several other fields.<br/><br/>

 						<span>Eligibility Criteria</span><br/><br/>
 						IN order to get admission on M.Tech (Mechanical Engineering) Course from the CGC Landran- Best College for M.Tech (ME) of Punjab then you must have B. Tech /B.E. degree in Mechanical engineering.<br/><br/>

 						<span>Admission Procedure</span><br/><br/>
 						All mechanical engineering seats are to be filled on the basis of percentage obtained by the candidate in B.Tech/B.E or the Score obtained by the candidate in Gate Examination. Admissions are done through online counseling carried out by PTU, Jalandhar.<br/><br/> 
